The existing Stock Island Marina Village is located at 7009 Shrimp Road on Stock Island
in the Florida Keys, Monroe County, Florida. The subject site is approximately 41 acres
and is located on the south (ocean) side of US 1 / Overseas Highway, near
Mile Marker 5. A Project Location Map is presented in Figure 1 on the following page.
The Stock Island Marina Village is proposing to redevelop and renovate portions of this
site with expanded facilities, new land uses and updated / enhanced amenities. A
preliminary site plan for this project is included in Appendix A of this report.
KBP Consulting, Inc. has been retained by Smith Oropeza, P.L. to prepare a traffic
impact study for this project in accordance with the Monroe County Traffic Report
Guidelines. This study addresses the anticipated trip generation and distribution
characteristics of the project, the current and future operating conditions of nearby
roadways / intersections, and project traffic impacts along US 1 / Overseas Highway by
mile marker. A traffic analysis methodology meeting was held with Monroe County’s
traffic engineering consultant and a summary of this discussion is presented in
It is noted that the proposed development program has been modified since the initial traffic analysis
methodology was developed in June 2014. The restaurant and additional marina berths are no longer
proposed as part of this application.
As mentioned previously, the size of the subject site is approximately 41 acres with
approximately 29 acres being submerged. The site currently consists of a marina with
offices (5,024 square feet) and 361 permitted wet slips, a 7,938 square foot industrial
building containing an engine service business and an artists’ workshop, a public dog
park, a community garden, and a 7,704 square foot building for the artist’s cooperative.
Various marina-related amenities are also provided on site including a ship’s store, a
fitness center, and laundry / bathhouse facilities.
Vehicular access to the existing Stock Island Marina Village is provided via Shrimp Road

The proposed expansion and redevelopment on this site will consist of 100 new transient
dwelling units (i.e. hotel rooms), and a 10,000 square foot building that will be used for
marine service (5,000 square feet of industrial marine repair shop), a fish house
(1,000 square feet of specialty retail) and fish house packing and distribution facilities
(4,000 square feet of light industrial). Various hotel and marina related amenities (or
common areas) will be provided including a ship’s store, a restaurant with tiki bar, and
swimming pool. There will be no increase in the number of wet slips.
Vehicular access to the site will be generally consistent with the current configuration.

The link analysis compares the maximum number of reserve trips on US 1 / Overseas
Highway through the Stock Island area (per Monroe County’s Level of Service and
Reserve Capacity Table) with the project’s traffic impacts. Based upon a 60% / 25% /
15% trip distribution, the project will add a maximum of 524 daily trips (60% of the
additional 873 daily trips) to Segment Number 1 (Stock Island). Based upon a review of
the traffic studies prepared for the aforementioned committed projects to be located on
Stock Island (i.e. CVS, Oceanside, and Key West Harbor Yacht Club), the committed
traffic impact of this project on Segment Number 1 is 1,460 trips. Therefore, the total
impact of these projects on Segment Number 1 is 1,984 trips.
According to Monroe County’s Level of Service and Reserve Capacity Table
(see Appendix I), Segment Number 1 has a maximum reserve volume of 2,022 trips.
Therefore, US 1 / Overseas Highway through Stock Island has sufficient capacity to
absorb the maximum impacts generated by the Stock Island Marina Village project.

page.text: For this project, it was assumed that the typical maximum trip length will be
approximately five (5) miles to the west (to Key West) and 50 miles to the east (toward
Marathon). The average trip length was assumed to be one-half (1/2) of the maximum
trip length in either direction, or 3 miles to the west and 25 miles to the east.
Based upon these trip length assumptions, the US 1 / Overseas Highway segments
identified in Monroe County’s Traffic Report Guidelines, and the traffic assignment
discussed previously, an estimate of the number of primary trips by segment on US 1 /
Overseas Highway was performed. Table 5 summarizes the number of primary trips by
segment on US 1/ Overseas Highway (Arterial Trip Assignment). As indicated in this
table, this project will add approximately 873 daily trips.
